Pygidium rounded with three anal cirri; two cirri very long, filiform, placed on latero-ventral side; one cirrus short, located mid-ventrally; anal aperture on dorsal side (
Fig. 43G
).

Remarks.
The morphology of the specimens of 

Aricidea claudiae

from the Sea of Marmara resembles the original and subsequent descriptions of the species (
Laubier & Ramos 1974
; 
Strelzov 1979
; 
Aguirrezabalaga & Gil 2009
).
